From b5ddc35de515fc96ee5517c2e3d1f4022c1ddf8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 18:33:31 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 07/14] chronium: per-profile
 screen.{width,height,availWidth,availHeight,colorDepth} + devicePixelRatio

Patches Screen and LocalDOMWindow so JS sees the profile's screen
geometry instead of the host monitor's. width/height/availWidth/
availHeight/colorDepth flow through Screen.cc, devicePixelRatio
through LocalDOMWindow.cc. pixelDepth follows colorDepth (per spec).

Plumbing: FingerprintProfile::ScreenCsv serialises the JSON 'screen'
dict to 'W,H,AW,AH,CD,DPR'; AppendExtraCommandLineSwitches forwards
it as --fingerprint-screen; the renderer parses in
RenderThreadStarted and installs into blink::FingerprintState's new
ScreenFp struct, which the patched blink getters read at top
priority (before any DomWindow/Settings-based override).

ScreenFp is POD so storage uses a plain function-local static
(base::NoDestructor would static-assert on the trivial destructor).

Verified with two profiles:
  profile A: 1920x1080 / avail 1920x1040 / depth 24 / dpr 1
  profile B: 1366x768 / avail 1366x728 / depth 30 / dpr 1.25

Files touched:
- chrome/common/chrome_switches.{h,cc}                 (kFingerprintScreen)
- chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.{h,cc} (ScreenCsv)
- chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc      (append switch)
- chrome/renderer/chrome_content_renderer_client.cc    (parse + install)
- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fingerprint/
    fingerprint_state.{h,cc}                           (ScreenFp + setter/getter)
- third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc      (5 getters)
